parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent ABS Brake Pedal Hardness and Vehicle Veering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent hardness of the ABS brake pedal can cause the vehicle to veer to the right or left, leading to loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard and resists application
the vehicle veers to the right or left when brakes are applied
extended stopping distance on wet pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the safety of the vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Gasoline leaks from the fuel tank
fuel smell or odor inside or outside the vehicle
fuel droplets or puddles under the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: the airbag light flashes on and off
no apparent problem despite the warning light.
